<h2 id="_1_info_revenue_by_referrer_per_item">1. 1) Info: revenue by referrer per item</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This statistic shows how much <strong>revenue</strong> was generated by each item <strong>referrer</strong>. Furthermore, it shows which <strong>percentage</strong> of the total revenue each referrer generated. As an alternative to selecting a certain predefined time span, you can also choose an individual <strong>start</strong> and <strong>end date</strong>. Default setting for the <strong>time span</strong>: the <strong>last 30 days</strong>. Default setting of the <strong>status section</strong>: from <strong>status 1</strong> to <strong>status 7</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_2_details_about_the_statistic">2. 2) Details about the statistic</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>revenue in Euro</strong> will be displayed for each <strong>item referrer</strong> within the selected <strong>time span</strong>. If an item referrer did not generate any revenue, then this referrer will not be displayed. The <strong>item referrer</strong>, the corresponding <strong>revenue in Euro</strong> and the <strong>percentage of total revenue</strong> will be displayed as <strong>information in a mouseover</strong> (see image 1). In this statistic you can see, e.g. which referrers generated a large amount of revenue. Conversely, you can also see which referrers generated little or no revenue.</p>
</div>
